event.title: Elysian Fields
event.description:
Doors 6:30 p.m. / Show 7:30 p.m.
$15 advance / $17 day of show
18+

Legendary cult heroes Elysian Fields have always travelled in mysterious waters. Led by the enigmatic New York co-composers Jennifer Charles (vocals) and Oren Bloedow (guitar), the music born of their collaboration is impossible to categorize. They carry a torch for nature, sex, love, the cycle of death and rebirth, and the sounds of folk and jazz ballads, no wave and classical music, seamlessly interwoven into a style that is at once languorously romantic and tough. Long known to European audiences where they have been lionized, the paradox is that in their home country, their art has gone largely unnoticed, but to the musical cognoscenti and in the know music Hop-heads.

For more information or to purchase tickets, please visit

event.title: The Cure presents "Reflections"
event.description:
"REFLECTIONS" sees an evolving line up of band members past and present playing the first three Cure albums live in their entirety - from the punchy, offbeat, starkly unadorned songs of Three Imaginary Boys (1979), through the increasingly shadowy and quixotic pieces of Seventeen Seconds (1980), to the singular melancholic grandeur of Faith (1981) - in a truly extraordinary concert experience.


SET 1: Three Imaginary Boys (1979)
The Cure Trio: Robert Smith (voice & guitar), Simon Gallup (bass), Jason Cooper (drums)

SET 2: Seventeen Seconds (1980)
The Cure Quartet: Robert Smith (voice & guitar), Simon Gallup (bass), Jason Cooper (drums), Roger O’Donnell (keys)

SET 3: Faith (1981)
The Cure Quintet: Robert Smith (voice & guitar), Simon Gallup (bass), Jason Cooper (drums), Roger O’Donnell (keys & percussion), Laurence Tolhurst (keys & percussion)

SET 4: ‘Encores’

event.title: Thriller Live: Tribute to Michael Jackson
event.description:
Michael Jackson
Thriller Live: Tribute to Michael Jackson is a spectacular high energy multimedia production moonwalking at the Black Box Theater bringing Michael Jackson's chart-cresting classic music alive. The show includes Michael Jackson chart-toppers from best-selling albums including Off the Wall, Thriller, Bad, and Dangerous in this electrifying revival of Pop Music's Royal Highness. The themes of love, peace, unity and harmony are presented in the show during the Thankgsgiving holiday weekend. Featuring talented artists and performers and an ensemble of dancers who will portray Michael at different stages of his amazing career, mastering his unique dancing to perform such hits as "Billie Jean," "Thriller," "Smooth Criminal" "Remember the Time," "Bad," and many more....Join the ultimate MJ event/party complete with an all-star dance company, video jockeys, and illusionists in newly expanded, never before seen skits (entirely original in content) complete with synchronized dance routines, classic music video recreations, Jacksons' costumes and performance art -- add up to must-see entertainment this holiday season!

event.title: The Dog & Pony Show presents: DJ Garth
event.description:
We're about to get real strange. You know how awkward it usually gets around the holidays? This year we decided to step it up a notch. We found a shady hole in Willy-b covered with furry walls, dead animals, musty smells, a bunch of broken stuff, awkward lighting, creepy visuals, and music by the bizarre west coast talents of the legendary DJ Garth. Come dressed in the freakiest gear you can find. (If you don't dress weird already). For more inspiration please visit: http://accidentalchinesehipsters.tumblr.com/

FRIDAY NOVEMBER 25th
The Dog & Pony Show presents...

Episode #014: "WEIRDSGIVING"

starring...

-DJ GARTH [grayhound recordings | wicked sf]
I don't even know where to begin. With a career spanning over two decades of relentless debauchery, Garth is the truth. Conscious hell raising that has been going down in LA, SF, a ten year residency at Come Unity, thirteen legendary years with the Wicked Sound System, Back2Back jams w/ right hand man Jeno and Thomas Bullock, legendary nights with the Wicked crew and a recent world tour with Harvey - Garth's resume is too extensive to be summed up in this short blurb. His fusion of Acid House, Psyche Disco & Space Rock ushered in an era of Rave hysteria that ripped through the west coast and spread all the way east to NYC and everywhere in between. If they gave an award for 'Most cool Shit Accomplished in House Music', Garth would be the recipient. It's a real honor to bring him back two our little city of Brooklyn, should be a night to remember! http://www.grayhound.net/

-TAIMUR AGHA [blk|market membership]
This one has been a long time coming. Techno music revolutionary, nightlife renaissance man, Blk|market Membership co-founder and creator of some of the most beautiful nights of underground music in New York City present. Taimur is as real as it gets. There aren't many who's love of top notch production and dedication to bringing people to a higher state of musical conscience supersedes Taimur's. He's one in a million, and his passion comes through so vividly in his track selection and programming. http://blkmarketmembership.com/

-PAUL RAFFAELE [the dog & pony show]
He's quicker with the mix then a Samurai with the sword. His music is SO NEW, that he actually has tracks before producers make them. He's the alpha male in the dog & pony family and head of the household, even though none of us are related. Come down and watch daddy work. http://dogandponynyc.com/

-KEVIN OSHA [the lost borough crew]
Our favorite part about KO is his unique style. People throw around 'unique style' real often, but everyone else just talks nonsense. We're on some real shit. Influences from straight 90s New York tech-house raw flavor. Osha has musical-swagger. He's like the James Dean of House Music, the Don Quixote of Techno. Hide your kids, hide your wife. Dazit. http://www.residentadvisor.net/dj/kevinosha

event.description:

10:00pm

$10 // 21+

BOUNCE is a monthly house party created by a collective of DJs and producers who are bringing fresh, top notch dance music to NYC, spinning flavors of funk, soul, jackin and tech house.

In a diluted dance music scene, BOUNCE is bringing back what matters most: the music and the people...The resident DJ's and their guests draw a savvy crowd full of dancers, artists and producers.
resident DJs Joe Pompeo, Mike Stefan and DJ Syne
The BOUNCE residents are from a variety of backgrounds. Joe Pompeo, producer and engineer, has had a number of top ten releases on Salted Music, BlockHead and Nervous Recordings. Mike Stefan, former record store buyer, keeps his selection fresh and has been rocking crowds from NYC to Ukraine since 2002. DJ Syne, just back from playing Manila, rounds out the crew and brings a deeper edge to the party.

event.description:
Friday, November 25th, 2011

21+

GUEST LIST (get on it by going to www.freedomdanceparty.com)
ladies free before 12am, $10 all night after
fellas $10 before 2am, $15 after


GENERAL ADMISSION
ladies $15, guys $20

The Freedom Party NYC is New York City's longest running weekly Friday night dance party. Recently the winner of Papermag's highly coveted award for "Best Party of 2010 (Peoples Choice)," and runner up in URB Magazine's "Best Party of 2010" (nationwide), Freedom was created in 2002 by Herbert Holler, DJ Cosi and Marc Smooth. Their mission was to bring music back to the forefront of nightlife, and to provide a weekly home for people from all walks of life to dance and be free, regardless of who you know, what you wear or how much money you make. Playing an incredibly tight of mix of danceable hits from the 60s through today, including hip-hop, R&B, rock, reggae, soul,New Wave, house music, salsa, merengue, electro, Afrobeat and more, the Freedom Party NYC continues to fill its dance floor each week with people from all over the globe.
